WEBVTT

00:02.077 --> 00:09.008
♪

00:09.159 --> 00:13.253
<i> Olivia: They tell you</i>
<i> when one door closes</i>

00:13.347 --> 00:15.014
<i> Another opens.</i>

00:21.338 --> 00:23.605
<i> But what if you can't say</i>
<i> goodbye to the past?</i>

00:24.600 --> 00:25.441
[loud knocking]

00:40.875 --> 00:42.291
[sobs]

00:46.955 --> 00:48.130
[crash]

00:51.794 --> 00:54.553
<i> Olivia: Because it's always</i>
<i> staring back at you.</i>

00:57.224 --> 00:59.058
<i> Haunting you.</i>

01:01.620 --> 01:04.897
♪

01:16.302 --> 01:17.076
[gasps]

01:17.303 --> 01:19.703
[doors slam]

01:20.973 --> 01:23.565
I would like to speak
with olivia alone.

01:23.584 --> 01:28.587
You do not get to make requests
after breaking our agreement.

01:28.738 --> 01:34.409
Knocking on my door,
threatening to wake my family.

01:34.428 --> 01:35.836
You do not get to see
my daughter,

01:35.930 --> 01:37.888
Not tonight, not ever.

01:39.491 --> 01:40.340
You must believe me,

01:40.492 --> 01:41.992
I am not here to exhume
our past.

01:42.085 --> 01:43.660
I am here to put it
to rest.

01:43.753 --> 01:44.937
Well then why come at all?

01:48.109 --> 01:49.775
Because I have cancer.

01:55.932 --> 01:58.933
And christopher...

01:59.027 --> 02:01.011
He's in medical school now.

02:01.104 --> 02:04.197
Can you believe it,
my son the doctor.

02:04.350 --> 02:06.199
You must realize how dire
things are for me

02:06.352 --> 02:09.019
To be on your doorstep.

02:09.037 --> 02:10.295
I have little time left

02:10.522 --> 02:13.281
And even less of the inheritance
garland left me.

02:13.300 --> 02:15.542
It was all lost
in the crash.

02:15.636 --> 02:19.471
And when I'm gone, christopher
will have nowhere to go.

02:19.698 --> 02:21.531
No means to finish
his schooling,

02:21.625 --> 02:24.384
No other family
to support him.

02:24.536 --> 02:27.896
I gave you my daughter
by choice.

02:30.209 --> 02:33.710
Tonight I am asking you
to take my son.

02:33.803 --> 02:35.320
<i> Olivia: I had followed</i>
<i> my instincts</i>

02:35.547 --> 02:37.781
<i> But that had led straight</i>
<i> to mal's death.</i>

02:39.401 --> 02:40.975
Olivia, please.

02:41.069 --> 02:42.736
<i> Olivia: And so it began.</i>

02:42.888 --> 02:46.331
<i>For one dark year I pushed back</i>
<i> against my instincts.</i>

02:46.558 --> 02:48.792
This is malcolm's decision
to make.

02:52.339 --> 02:55.132
<i> Olivia: And learn to follow</i>
<i> malcolm's instead.</i>

02:57.661 --> 03:02.739
Nothing will be free
for him here.

03:02.832 --> 03:05.475
He will have to work
for his education.

03:12.359 --> 03:13.841
But I don't need
a tutor, daddy.

03:13.861 --> 03:15.419
I just want to go back to school
and see my friends.

03:15.437 --> 03:16.361
Sit.

03:18.515 --> 03:20.991
<i> Olivia: I became an observer</i>
<i> in my own home.</i>

03:22.428 --> 03:24.945
<i> [playing piano]</i>
<i> ♪</i>

03:25.039 --> 03:27.355
<i> Malcolm: None of this goddamn</i>
<i> piano music!</i>

03:27.449 --> 03:29.357
You know what I want
for christmas?!

03:29.376 --> 03:31.601
Silence!

03:31.695 --> 03:33.620
<i> Olivia: I told myself</i>
<i> that I did it for the safety</i>
<i> of my children.</i>

03:33.772 --> 03:35.464
<i> Malcolm: ...In here,</i>
<i> day in and day out.</i>

03:54.401 --> 03:56.460
Alicia has died.

03:57.629 --> 04:01.240
<i> Olivia: I thought that as long</i>
<i> as I obeyed malcolm...</i>

04:01.467 --> 04:02.983
Where do you think christopher
would like

04:03.135 --> 04:04.651
This picture of his parents?

04:04.803 --> 04:07.729
<i> Olivia: One thing could</i>
<i> remain certain.</i>

04:07.823 --> 04:11.833
<i>That what happened to mal would</i>
<i> never happen again in my home.</i>

04:13.645 --> 04:15.312
Mother?

04:15.405 --> 04:17.330
I thought perhaps
I could ride my horse

04:17.483 --> 04:18.590
Into town this afternoon.

04:18.817 --> 04:20.333
If this is about your debutante
ball dress,

04:20.486 --> 04:22.261
I already have appointments
set for seamstresses

04:22.412 --> 04:24.412
To come to the house
next week.

04:24.431 --> 04:26.172
Then shouldn't I know what
the latest fashions are

04:26.325 --> 04:27.657
Before they arrive?

04:27.676 --> 04:29.083
[sighs]

04:29.103 --> 04:31.085
You can't keep me locked up
in this house forever.

04:31.179 --> 04:32.688
It's up to your father.

04:42.283 --> 04:43.198
[knocking at door]

04:46.453 --> 04:47.677
Daddy...

04:47.771 --> 04:49.529
With my debutante ball
coming up

04:49.623 --> 04:52.516
I really need to have the best
dress, don't you think?

04:52.534 --> 04:54.367
Well, only the best
for my daughter

04:54.461 --> 04:57.871
On the night she introduces
herself to virginian society.

04:57.965 --> 05:00.206
So, maybe you could give me
the key to the swan room

05:00.301 --> 05:02.042
And I could have a look through
grandmother's old things

05:02.136 --> 05:06.212
For some inspiration.

05:06.365 --> 05:10.050
Why don't you visit the shops
in town instead?

05:10.202 --> 05:11.643
I don't know, daddy.

05:11.795 --> 05:13.720
It just doesn't sound very fun
to go all the way there

05:13.872 --> 05:15.981
And look at all those
tantalizing things

05:16.208 --> 05:19.543
And not have any means to bring
any of them home.

05:19.561 --> 05:23.822
Well, what is to be done
about that, hmm?

05:27.644 --> 05:30.329
<i> [piano playing in</i>
<i> the background]</i>

05:41.658 --> 05:43.917
I guess I could ask joel
to stop playing his piano

05:44.011 --> 05:45.660
For a bit and take me.

05:45.679 --> 05:48.347
Wouldn't that be a gift
to us all.

06:01.603 --> 06:08.108
♪

06:08.202 --> 06:10.276
I've already lost my closest
friendships from school

06:10.429 --> 06:12.371
Since no one writes anymore.

06:12.598 --> 06:14.764
When they show up to my ball,
if they even do,

06:14.783 --> 06:16.023
I'll be a complete stranger.

06:16.118 --> 06:17.934
How am I going to have
any fun?

06:17.953 --> 06:19.769
Well, hopefully this christopher
fellow coming to stay

06:19.788 --> 06:21.771
Will make father look up.

06:21.790 --> 06:23.882
It's easy for you to see
the positives.

06:24.033 --> 06:26.610
They actually let you leave
for school

06:26.703 --> 06:28.369
And get away with a life
full of secret dalliances

06:28.463 --> 06:29.704
While I'm stuck at home

06:29.798 --> 06:31.464
Listening to the world
on the radio.

06:31.617 --> 06:34.059
No, that's just because
since mal died.

06:36.121 --> 06:38.805
Well, father's the only one
making decisions these days

06:38.957 --> 06:41.641
And he doesn't give a fig
what happens to me.

06:41.793 --> 06:43.568
And it's dalliance.

06:43.795 --> 06:45.386
Singular.

06:45.406 --> 06:47.147
You're cruel.

06:47.299 --> 06:49.491
Why won't you tell me
about her?

06:51.987 --> 06:53.895
This is more fun.

06:53.914 --> 06:55.997
[laughs]

07:01.088 --> 07:02.904
Just tell me this.

07:02.998 --> 07:04.589
Is it because I know her?

07:04.741 --> 07:07.175
You can keep trying but you're
not getting anything out of me.

07:11.265 --> 07:14.007
Mrs. Steiner.
Good afternoon.

07:14.101 --> 07:17.494
Why mr. Joel foxworth.

07:17.587 --> 07:21.681
All grown up and pretty
as a peacock.

07:21.833 --> 07:25.444
If you'll excuse me,
some of us don't have time
to dawdle in the streets

07:25.671 --> 07:29.614
Contributing absolutely nothing
to the workforce.

07:36.105 --> 07:38.123
And who was that bucket
of joy?

07:38.274 --> 07:40.533
A bucket and a mop
full of joy.

07:40.627 --> 07:43.186
She used to be our housekeeper,
mrs. Steiner.

07:43.205 --> 07:46.280
Mother fired her
before you were born.

07:46.300 --> 07:48.191
Mal always told me how much
he hated her.

07:48.210 --> 07:50.543
Hmm, I can't imagine why.

07:50.637 --> 07:53.046
Do you want to come with me
and help pick out a dress?

07:53.140 --> 07:55.640
Tempting, but I have
my own shopping to do.

08:07.303 --> 08:10.714
Oh, miss foxworth,
your stockings.

08:10.732 --> 08:11.990
Ugh.

08:12.217 --> 08:14.217
Just another thing falling apart
in my world.

08:14.310 --> 08:15.902
Do you have any
for purchase?

08:16.054 --> 08:17.913
Well, only paint on.

08:19.574 --> 08:20.457
[sighs]

08:37.851 --> 08:39.768
Looking for something?

08:43.582 --> 08:45.915
Not anymore.

08:46.009 --> 08:48.918
Sir, I'm helping
the young lady.

08:48.937 --> 08:50.695
That's quite all right.

08:53.700 --> 08:55.108
The top button seems
to have caught

08:55.260 --> 08:58.370
As I was unloading my luggage
on the train.

08:58.521 --> 09:00.688
Normally I wouldn't mind
being one button short,

09:00.707 --> 09:04.450
But first impressions
being what they are.

09:04.545 --> 09:08.605
If the lady will allow, I can
mend it in just a moment.

09:08.623 --> 09:10.790
Go right ahead.

09:10.942 --> 09:12.384
And take your time.

09:20.727 --> 09:23.787
We seem to have stumbled upon
each other indisposed, miss.

09:23.805 --> 09:28.883
And exposed, sir.

09:28.902 --> 09:31.570
I'll forgive your bad impression
if you forgive mine.

09:31.797 --> 09:32.571
Deal.

09:35.133 --> 09:36.223
[sighs]

09:36.243 --> 09:38.818
Those were my last silk pair.

09:38.912 --> 09:40.486
Were?

09:40.639 --> 09:42.322
They ripped.

09:42.474 --> 09:44.474
I guess I am to become
one of the many women

09:44.567 --> 09:46.734
Parading about town
with painted seams

09:46.753 --> 09:49.087
On the back of
their bare legs.

09:49.238 --> 09:54.075
It's unladylike
and uncomfortable.

09:54.094 --> 09:56.152
Well, I may not be able to
soothe the issue of comfort

09:56.245 --> 09:57.745
But I can assure you
that no gentleman

09:57.764 --> 10:00.223
Will be staring
at your legs.

10:03.586 --> 10:06.354
So, you're saying
you're no gentleman?

10:15.949 --> 10:17.115
Thank you.

10:26.868 --> 10:28.943
I'm forever in your debt.

10:28.962 --> 10:30.370
[small laugh]

10:30.522 --> 10:33.373
Better watch out.
I might keep you to that.

10:33.467 --> 10:34.966
[laughs]

11:02.721 --> 11:06.239
<i> [playing piano skillfully]</i>
<i> ♪</i>

11:06.391 --> 11:21.254
<i> ♪</i>

11:21.406 --> 11:36.361
<i> ♪</i>

11:36.588 --> 11:41.866
There you are. I have
a present for you,

11:42.018 --> 11:43.952
So you know what time it is
to come to see me.

11:50.285 --> 11:53.027
But I like listening
for your music.

11:53.121 --> 11:56.122
It reminds me of when nella
used to sing to me at night.

11:56.216 --> 12:00.051
You can still listen with a very
handsome watch on your arm.

12:02.222 --> 12:05.223
You sure this isn't just some
way to hold me over longer?

12:05.450 --> 12:07.392
You know my father.

12:07.543 --> 12:09.728
There's no way I'm getting
my trust till I turn 25.

12:09.879 --> 12:11.304
I don't need some
rich man's fortune

12:11.456 --> 12:14.640
Making me wait to go see
the world.

12:14.793 --> 12:17.218
I'll go out
and grab it myself.

12:17.237 --> 12:19.237
Okay.

12:19.388 --> 12:21.555
Where is it you truly
want to go?

12:21.575 --> 12:23.557
North.

12:23.577 --> 12:26.227
[laughs]

12:26.321 --> 12:28.321
What does that mean?

12:28.415 --> 12:32.751
New york? Chicago?

12:32.978 --> 12:35.478
Nova scotia?

12:35.497 --> 12:39.591
You can't just traipse the globe
without any direction.

12:39.742 --> 12:43.653
I'll be happy anywhere
without automobiles to work on.

12:43.746 --> 12:46.990
Anywhere I can make
my own decisions,

12:47.008 --> 12:49.993
Just anywhere but here.

12:50.086 --> 12:52.419
[whispers]
traveling costs money.

12:52.514 --> 12:54.847
I can take odd jobs.

12:55.000 --> 12:57.850
You can always play your music
for money.

12:57.944 --> 13:01.170
Everyone needs music.

13:01.189 --> 13:03.856
I can't take my piano
with me.

13:04.009 --> 13:06.267
There's plenty of places
got pianos

13:06.361 --> 13:10.104
And you're plenty pretty
to get a job playing on them.

13:10.123 --> 13:11.706
Aren't you kind.

13:27.048 --> 13:29.474
Would you please quit
that racket?!!

13:40.061 --> 13:42.612
[whispers]
go, go, go.

13:45.216 --> 13:47.450
[breathing shakily]

13:49.329 --> 13:51.888
I told you all that piano
playing would make him soft.

13:51.906 --> 13:53.389
What are you talking about?

13:53.482 --> 13:56.650
I found that negro garage boy

13:56.670 --> 13:59.003
Doing improper things
to your son.

13:59.155 --> 14:00.505
Oh my god,
is he hurt?

14:00.656 --> 14:02.841
Worse. He was enjoying it.

14:07.589 --> 14:09.405
I'll talk to him.

14:09.424 --> 14:12.433
I will take care of it.
You've already done enough.

14:19.267 --> 14:20.249
[door breaking]

14:20.768 --> 14:22.268
Hey, hey, what's going on?

14:22.420 --> 14:25.771
Hey! Hey!

14:25.924 --> 14:26.680
<i> Nella: What's happening?</i>

14:26.700 --> 14:29.367
No! You gotta have
a reason!

14:29.594 --> 14:33.446
-Just tell us why!
-Mom, they're hurting him.

14:33.598 --> 14:35.765
Nella: You can't just break
in our home!

14:35.858 --> 14:37.691
Samuel: You get your hands off
my boy.

14:37.711 --> 14:39.952
-You gotta have a reason!
-Mom, where are they taking him?

14:40.105 --> 14:41.379
Samuel: Get off him!

14:41.530 --> 14:44.132
Let's go. Get in the truck.
We'll follow them!

14:49.205 --> 14:50.889
Come on, come on!
Get in, get in!

14:54.135 --> 14:56.019
[siren blaring]

14:59.307 --> 15:02.150
[siren blaring]

15:09.242 --> 15:11.743
Oh, my god! Harry!

15:17.475 --> 15:18.917
You get your hands off me!
Don't touch me!

15:19.144 --> 15:19.918
[struggling grunts]

15:22.647 --> 15:23.421
<i> Harry: Get off me!</i>

15:24.315 --> 15:25.423
Is this him?

15:32.748 --> 15:34.340
That's him all right.
That's the thief.

15:34.492 --> 15:36.325
I ain't no thief. I didn't
steal nothing.

15:36.419 --> 15:39.086
You shut your month.
Not another word.

15:39.105 --> 15:41.773
Our harry,
he is no thief.

15:41.924 --> 15:43.274
Then how do you explain
this spiffy little piece

15:43.426 --> 15:44.943
On his wrist then?

15:46.095 --> 15:47.761
Mrs. Foxworth,
you know our harry

15:47.855 --> 15:50.339
Would never steal
from anyone.

15:50.433 --> 15:53.176
She can speak
to his character.

15:53.194 --> 15:54.601
Please.

15:54.621 --> 15:56.120
I don't think we know this boy
well enough

15:56.272 --> 15:57.604
To speak to his character.

15:57.699 --> 15:58.605
[furiously]
oh, come on!

15:58.625 --> 15:59.532
Samuel don't!

15:59.626 --> 16:01.960
Mrs. Foxworth, please!

16:06.466 --> 16:08.374
I didn't do anything!

16:08.526 --> 16:09.300
Harry, stop moving.

16:09.527 --> 16:10.284
No, no, no!

16:10.378 --> 16:11.043
[lands heavy punch]

16:11.137 --> 16:12.878
[screaming]
no!!!

16:12.973 --> 16:16.457
No, harry! Please no!

16:16.476 --> 16:18.476
[sobbing uncontrollably]

16:19.220 --> 16:20.979
[sobbing]
harry!

16:22.056 --> 16:24.816
♪

16:26.377 --> 16:27.276
Olivia: Get inside.

16:31.640 --> 16:32.991
Well done.

16:40.225 --> 16:40.999
[sobbing]

16:49.584 --> 16:51.417
[siren wailing]

16:51.511 --> 16:54.161
[all sobbing]

16:54.255 --> 16:56.431
Let's go, let's go.
Let's go.

17:11.031 --> 17:14.757
Does anyone want to tell me
what really happened last night?

17:14.776 --> 17:16.284
Drop it, corrine.

17:17.945 --> 17:19.537
I hate it here.

17:20.431 --> 17:22.040
[door opens]

17:22.191 --> 17:25.793
Mr. And mrs. Foxworth.
Your guest has arrived.

17:35.947 --> 17:37.388
Christopher.

17:43.212 --> 17:46.806
Welcome back to foxworth hall.

17:46.958 --> 17:51.235
Corrine, joel, I'd like you
to meet your uncle christopher.

17:55.800 --> 18:00.161
Pleasure to finally meet you,
uncle christopher.

18:02.640 --> 18:04.473
Uh, yes.

18:04.492 --> 18:05.917
Pleasure.

18:20.158 --> 18:23.326
Christopher, we're delighted
to have you here.

18:23.344 --> 18:25.103
Isn't that right?

18:26.664 --> 18:28.106
Yes. Right.

18:32.094 --> 18:35.020
Please excuse joel's silence.

18:35.115 --> 18:37.615
He often plays the piano
too late into the night

18:37.766 --> 18:38.691
And tires himself.

18:38.843 --> 18:41.360
He's a very dedicated musician.

18:41.512 --> 18:43.287
Piano.

18:43.514 --> 18:45.030
Something I've always wanted
to learn.

18:45.183 --> 18:49.293
Actually, you already know how.
Or you did.

18:49.445 --> 18:53.856
I taught you along with both
of the boys ages ago.

18:53.875 --> 18:55.708
Well now...

18:55.860 --> 18:58.285
So joel, tell me.
Is it like muscle memory?

18:58.304 --> 18:59.528
Will I immediately
become beethoven

18:59.547 --> 19:02.456
If I just return my fingers
to the keys?

19:02.475 --> 19:04.308
Piano's not a bicycle.

19:09.056 --> 19:10.373
I'm so grateful

19:10.391 --> 19:12.483
That you're allowing me
to stay here with you.

19:12.710 --> 19:14.543
Your charity in providing me
a home,

19:14.562 --> 19:17.137
I can't thank you enough.

19:17.231 --> 19:19.806
Is that what you think this is?

19:19.826 --> 19:21.159
Charity?

19:21.386 --> 19:22.568
Malcolm.

19:22.662 --> 19:24.328
Of course not.

19:24.480 --> 19:27.665
I hope you are prepared to work
in exchange for your tuition.

19:27.816 --> 19:29.983
That is the arrangement
as I've understood it.

19:30.003 --> 19:31.485
And I am more than happy
to serve your office

19:31.579 --> 19:32.837
In any way it requires.

19:32.988 --> 19:34.563
You will not be working
in the office.

19:34.582 --> 19:38.843
You will be helping out with the
yard-work here at foxworth hall.

19:39.995 --> 19:42.588
I'd be happy to, sir.

19:42.740 --> 19:45.408
Daddy, surely you can't
expect him to work

19:45.426 --> 19:48.335
Alongside nella's family
and the rest of the servants.

19:48.429 --> 19:50.504
What's wrong with him working
alongside nella's family?

19:50.523 --> 19:51.914
Joel.

19:52.007 --> 19:54.192
You know mother?
You were right...

19:54.343 --> 19:56.101
I didn't get much rest
last night.

19:56.196 --> 19:57.653
Excuse me.

19:59.699 --> 20:01.032
It's for the best.

20:02.535 --> 20:04.035
I'm late for work.

20:07.707 --> 20:11.000
Corrine darling, why don't you
show your uncle to his room?

20:14.380 --> 20:17.440
I, um, haven't quite finished
my breakfast yet.

20:17.458 --> 20:19.458
I can surely find it myself.

20:19.610 --> 20:21.385
Come. I'll show you.

20:35.068 --> 20:37.693
♪

20:48.063 --> 20:50.915
[phone rings]

20:54.587 --> 20:56.812
Taylard residence.
Rockford speaking.

20:56.905 --> 21:00.925
Rock? It's corrine. Foxworth.

21:01.152 --> 21:04.169
And to what do I owe
the pleasure?

21:04.264 --> 21:08.933
How do you feel about
sneaking out this afternoon?

21:09.084 --> 21:12.661
I must say I did not expect this
house to be quite what it is,

21:12.755 --> 21:14.438
Or for you to be
who you are.

21:14.665 --> 21:16.332
Oh?

21:16.350 --> 21:19.926
Did your mother tell you
very much about her time here?

21:19.946 --> 21:23.355
Almost nothing at all.

21:23.508 --> 21:25.674
Is the piano the only instrument
I can play?

21:25.693 --> 21:26.617
[laughs weakly]

21:33.518 --> 21:34.792
I can't believe you're
allowing this.

21:34.943 --> 21:36.443
This isn't the place.

21:36.462 --> 21:38.629
You have to know what the police
would do to a black man

21:38.856 --> 21:41.299
They think stole from
a white man like father.

21:41.526 --> 21:42.466
[whispering]
keep your voice down.

21:42.618 --> 21:45.285
How can I when harry
could be dead?

21:45.379 --> 21:48.213
You saw what they did to him in
full view on our own front lawn.

21:48.366 --> 21:52.643
Just imagine what they're doing
to him in jail.

21:52.795 --> 21:55.646
We have to do something.

21:55.798 --> 21:58.891
This wasn't harry's fault.

21:58.985 --> 22:03.470
It's something we came to
together, willingly.

22:03.564 --> 22:05.156
It's what we both want.

22:09.162 --> 22:10.661
Where are you?

22:13.891 --> 22:17.501
Someone you love
is pleading with you

22:17.653 --> 22:21.839
That someone they love
is hurting.

22:21.990 --> 22:24.342
You won't do anything.

22:24.569 --> 22:25.801
Love?

22:28.739 --> 22:31.515
This isn't up to me.
It's up to your father.

22:36.414 --> 22:38.689
This is fine.
Don't go any further.

22:40.418 --> 22:42.526
Thanks for giving me a way
out of the house.

22:42.678 --> 22:45.104
That was the most exciting
afternoon I've had in weeks.

22:45.198 --> 22:46.364
Yeah. Yep.

22:46.515 --> 22:48.607
Movies always make me
feel better,

22:48.701 --> 22:52.185
Except when you make me wait
through the whole thing.

22:52.279 --> 22:57.616
I guess first year of business
school doesn't teach patience.

22:57.710 --> 22:59.935
Patience, no.

22:59.954 --> 23:02.438
Persistence, yes.

23:02.456 --> 23:07.793
I really do have to go.
I've been away for too long.

23:07.945 --> 23:10.796
I'm real glad you called me
up, corrine.

23:10.890 --> 23:12.556
See you soon.

23:18.564 --> 23:22.566
♪

23:29.150 --> 23:31.300
Corrine.
What you doing?

23:31.393 --> 23:35.579
Shh! It is none
of your business.

23:35.806 --> 23:37.306
But will you please,
please don't mention

23:37.399 --> 23:39.208
That you saw me to either
of my parents.

23:41.421 --> 23:43.162
As long as you tell me
where you were.

23:43.256 --> 23:44.088
Why do you care?

23:46.317 --> 23:48.092
Just concerned
for my niece.

23:50.671 --> 23:51.762
[sighs]

23:51.989 --> 23:54.323
So, my father has you
working already?

23:54.341 --> 23:56.659
Who am I to reject the call
of my new vocation?

23:56.752 --> 23:58.327
It does look as though
you'll be needing

23:58.420 --> 24:00.104
To pay another visit
to the seamstress.

24:00.331 --> 24:01.664
[laughs]

24:01.682 --> 24:03.757
Hey. Careful who you're
laughing at.

24:03.776 --> 24:05.668
See, I was just about
to tell you

24:05.686 --> 24:07.093
That your father's still
at the office

24:07.113 --> 24:10.022
And your mother is getting
her dress fitted.

24:10.116 --> 24:11.782
So, if you're looking
for a way to sneak in

24:11.934 --> 24:14.952
You might try through
the kitchen.

24:15.179 --> 24:18.013
But now maybe I won't
tell you that.

24:18.032 --> 24:19.248
Thank you.

24:26.524 --> 24:28.799
May I ask who this
is regarding?

24:28.951 --> 24:31.135
Not if you want to keep
your practice.

24:34.307 --> 24:39.643
And curtis, make it the most
effective treatment available.

24:50.715 --> 24:52.490
[typing]

25:03.394 --> 25:07.171
♪

25:09.066 --> 25:11.416
<i> Joel: Are you going to do</i>
<i> something about harry?</i>

25:11.569 --> 25:12.993
We are.

25:13.012 --> 25:14.136
Good.

25:15.330 --> 25:16.663
I'll come with you
to the station

25:16.682 --> 25:19.183
And you can drop the charges
against him immediately.

25:19.334 --> 25:21.243
You will be leaving
to spend some time

25:21.262 --> 25:24.930
At a professional facility
in westmoreland.

25:25.024 --> 25:29.843
Now you will say nothing
to your sister about this.

25:29.862 --> 25:35.032
You will pack one bag and I will
take you tonight after dark

25:35.183 --> 25:37.684
So nobody sees us.

25:37.778 --> 25:43.932
Now the professionals there
will... Get it out of you.

25:43.951 --> 25:49.029
And you will recover.
And then you will return.

25:49.048 --> 25:55.778
And we will never speak
of this again.

25:55.871 --> 25:57.279
What if I don't want to go?

25:57.372 --> 25:59.965
That is not your decision
to make.

26:00.059 --> 26:00.891
It's my life.

26:02.562 --> 26:04.395
It is my name.

26:06.566 --> 26:07.547
<i> [malcolm sighs]</i>

26:07.567 --> 26:08.899
And you're on board
with this?

26:12.220 --> 26:13.904
When are you going to tell me
what you want?!

26:16.967 --> 26:18.534
I am aligned
with your father.

26:24.992 --> 26:27.876
I'll go if you drop the charges
against harry.

26:34.485 --> 26:35.593
[sighs]

26:44.937 --> 26:46.103
[knocking at door]

26:49.442 --> 26:52.000
I know your father's plan
seems extreme.

26:52.094 --> 26:54.503
Your plan.
It's your plan too.

26:54.521 --> 26:57.356
You agreed to it.

26:57.450 --> 27:00.525
If you go get it fixed then
your father wouldn't hurt you.

27:00.678 --> 27:02.119
It's a little late for that.

27:03.364 --> 27:05.789
Thank you for doing this.

27:07.685 --> 27:09.460
I'm not doing this for you.

27:16.785 --> 27:19.428
The least you could do is
give this to harry for me.

27:34.228 --> 27:36.487
-I was just heading...
-Getting a glass of water.

27:38.732 --> 27:44.828
Because it's just so... Hot.

27:45.055 --> 27:47.814
Yes, it is.

27:47.833 --> 27:51.001
Exceptionally hot.

27:55.824 --> 27:58.008
[nervously]
well um... Goodnight.

28:02.831 --> 28:04.848
-That's not my room.
-That's my room.

28:07.669 --> 28:11.430
I will just go to
my actual room.

28:11.582 --> 28:16.435
Which is apparently
right next door to yours.

28:16.529 --> 28:17.528
[small laugh]

28:20.107 --> 28:21.031
Goodnight.

28:46.967 --> 28:51.395
<i> [melancholy music]</i>
<i> ♪</i>

28:51.622 --> 29:06.392
♪

29:06.412 --> 29:26.412
♪

29:26.432 --> 29:46.432
♪

29:46.452 --> 29:51.530
♪

29:51.682 --> 29:53.123
[sighs]

30:14.480 --> 30:18.390
[electricity buzzing]

30:18.542 --> 30:20.317
[whimpering in pain]

30:23.730 --> 30:28.492
[whimpering in pain]

30:39.229 --> 30:41.487
How did you sleep last night?

30:41.507 --> 30:43.582
-I was a bit restless.
-Not well at all.

30:43.676 --> 30:46.418
Of course. Sorry.

30:46.512 --> 30:49.012
No, it's okay.

30:49.239 --> 30:53.425
I slept just fine.
Thank you for asking.

30:53.519 --> 30:54.834
Where's joel?

30:54.854 --> 30:56.502
He left for montreal.

30:56.522 --> 30:57.479
What?

30:58.582 --> 30:59.690
Montreal?

31:01.251 --> 31:03.602
He received a telegram yesterday

31:03.754 --> 31:06.104
Inviting him to study
with a top musician there,

31:06.198 --> 31:10.275
But he had to leave right away
in order to accept.

31:10.427 --> 31:12.852
This is ridiculous.
Why wouldn't he tell me?

31:12.946 --> 31:15.263
Who's the musician?

31:15.282 --> 31:17.282
A composer at the philharmonic
there.

31:17.434 --> 31:20.193
He was really very torn
about it.

31:20.212 --> 31:22.771
He didn't want to upset you that
he'd be gone for the summer.

31:22.789 --> 31:25.883
He's not going to be back
in time for my ball?

31:26.110 --> 31:27.867
But he was supposed to be
my first dance.

31:27.887 --> 31:33.298
Your ball will be just as good
without him.

31:33.392 --> 31:34.683
Maybe better.

31:42.126 --> 31:46.028
♪

32:11.597 --> 32:13.430
Miss foxworth.

32:17.603 --> 32:19.937
Corrine, please.

32:20.088 --> 32:21.897
Glad to see you're home.

32:25.611 --> 32:28.570
I stopped reading when I
realized what they were.

32:31.675 --> 32:33.450
Oh, it's all right.

32:42.035 --> 32:44.853
I know you must be hurting.

32:44.946 --> 32:47.464
I just want to know
where he is.

32:47.615 --> 32:49.633
Did he tell you?

33:13.808 --> 33:19.888
What do you know about a place
called westmoreland sanitarium?

33:19.906 --> 33:23.166
Some physicians call
westmoreland experimental,

33:23.318 --> 33:28.413
But experimental is too kind
of a word for a place like that.

33:28.507 --> 33:30.340
What's happened?

33:32.160 --> 33:33.844
Over here, if you would be
so kind.

33:35.848 --> 33:36.905
Mrs. Foxworth.

33:37.850 --> 33:40.258
Do you have a moment?
We need to speak to you.

33:40.352 --> 33:41.409
It's important.

33:41.428 --> 33:43.186
I know about joel and harry.

33:44.672 --> 33:45.856
You may leave.

33:53.681 --> 33:56.015
Just what are you
both imagining?

33:56.109 --> 33:58.368
Forget imagination.

33:58.595 --> 34:00.612
Any serious professional
will tell you

34:00.764 --> 34:04.524
That westmoreland's methods
are extreme and unverified.

34:04.618 --> 34:06.859
They have consequences.

34:06.953 --> 34:09.546
The approach they're known
for uses shocks of electricity

34:09.697 --> 34:13.108
In patients' brains for every
condition you can imagine,

34:13.126 --> 34:17.203
From nervousness to venereal
disease to homo...

34:17.222 --> 34:18.722
Homosexuality.

34:20.801 --> 34:22.392
But it doesn't work.

34:26.565 --> 34:27.898
Mother, please.

34:30.569 --> 34:32.235
Joel needs you.

34:37.317 --> 34:41.244
♪

34:43.974 --> 34:45.082
<i> Olivia: I might have been</i>
<i> mourning mal</i>

34:45.309 --> 34:47.250
<i> But I had closed the door</i>
<i> on my joel</i>

34:47.477 --> 34:49.402
<i> Because I couldn't face</i>
<i> what was inside.</i>

34:49.421 --> 34:52.405
<i> But it was seeing him there,</i>
<i> what was left of him,</i>

34:52.499 --> 34:54.499
<i> I remembered who I was.</i>

34:54.651 --> 34:55.425
[gasps]

34:57.429 --> 34:58.887
<i> His provider.</i>

35:02.509 --> 35:03.934
<i> His protector.</i>

35:04.995 --> 35:05.936
Ma'am?

35:06.087 --> 35:06.937
<i> His parent.</i>

35:07.088 --> 35:08.513
What are you doing?

35:08.665 --> 35:10.774
Getting my son
out of this place.

35:10.925 --> 35:13.068
Only your husband
can sign him out.

35:18.283 --> 35:20.842
My husband doesn't need
to know anything about this.

35:20.935 --> 35:24.454
I am his mother and I'm
taking him home.

35:26.959 --> 35:29.367
Why do you think
they're taking so long?

35:29.519 --> 35:31.461
Everything's going to be
all right.

35:34.691 --> 35:36.299
If that place is what
I think it is,

35:36.451 --> 35:39.761
As soon as your mother sees joel
she'll know exactly what to do.

35:51.132 --> 35:52.874
[car engine rumbling]

35:52.893 --> 35:53.775
She's back.

35:57.322 --> 35:58.655
[knocking at door]

36:04.738 --> 36:06.571
It's joel.

36:06.665 --> 36:08.314
He's sick.

36:08.333 --> 36:10.167
I can't take care of him
in the house.

36:10.318 --> 36:12.652
Awful big house, though.

36:12.671 --> 36:15.655
I know how heavy this is
for me to show up like this.

36:15.674 --> 36:17.841
You don't know the first thing
about heavy.

36:17.992 --> 36:20.084
I should have done
more than I did.

36:20.179 --> 36:21.736
I wasn't myself.

36:21.755 --> 36:24.255
[teary] but I'm working on
finding that person again,

36:24.349 --> 36:26.999
And right now that person
is here at your door

36:27.019 --> 36:28.852
Asking for your help.

36:33.358 --> 36:35.266
I just want us all to sleep
better tonight.

36:35.419 --> 36:38.028
You want us to help
your boy.

36:38.179 --> 36:41.681
What work did you do
to help ours?

36:41.700 --> 36:43.533
She got him back for us.

36:43.760 --> 36:45.443
Beaten bad.

36:45.595 --> 36:46.444
Alive.

36:46.538 --> 36:49.021
No, I didn't.

36:49.041 --> 36:52.042
I was too much of a coward.
That was joel.

36:52.269 --> 36:53.859
Joel brought your son
back to you.

36:53.879 --> 36:58.715
So, if you won't do this for me,
would you do it for him?

37:06.132 --> 37:08.616
Where's your boy?

37:08.710 --> 37:11.302
He's laid out in the car.
I need a hand.

37:11.455 --> 37:13.855
Malcolm can never know.

37:34.902 --> 37:36.253
Oh, dear lord.

37:39.332 --> 37:40.215
I'll take the legs.

37:56.349 --> 37:58.108
What did you do to him?

38:43.897 --> 38:45.897
Has anyone heard from joel?

38:46.049 --> 38:49.659
I'd just like to make sure
he arrived in montreal safely.

38:53.573 --> 38:57.241
I'm sure he has.
Isn't that right, malcolm?

38:57.336 --> 38:59.127
I should get to work.

39:02.065 --> 39:03.840
As should I.

39:17.689 --> 39:19.097
[harshly] if you can't keep
this a secret...

39:19.191 --> 39:21.191
He was barely conscious.

39:21.342 --> 39:25.269
He needs to be in our home with
a real nurse or in a hospital.

39:25.364 --> 39:28.531
Do you want your father
to put him through a window?

39:29.943 --> 39:32.260
You let this happen.

39:32.278 --> 39:33.519
You lied to me.

39:33.613 --> 39:35.279
To protect you.

39:35.374 --> 39:38.023
You have no idea what's gone on
in this house,

39:38.043 --> 39:39.191
What I've done to shield you.

39:39.211 --> 39:41.769
I have never asked
to be shielded!

39:41.863 --> 39:43.546
When have you ever asked
what I wanted?!

39:43.773 --> 39:46.124
Everything I've done
was for you.

39:46.276 --> 39:48.009
And look at what we've lost.

40:04.051 --> 40:06.903
[horse whinnies]

40:20.585 --> 40:23.586
[thunder crashing]

40:23.738 --> 40:25.313
I'm worried about corrine.

40:25.331 --> 40:26.906
We had a fight.

40:26.925 --> 40:30.818
She rode off on her horse
just before the storm hit.

40:30.837 --> 40:32.503
I thought she'd be back
before dark.

40:32.656 --> 40:33.930
What were you thinking?

40:44.592 --> 40:47.092
[thunder crashing]

40:47.187 --> 40:49.854
<i> Malcolm:</i>
<i> Search the entire estate!</i>

40:50.006 --> 40:53.867
<i> Olivia: That night, horrors</i>
<i> rained down on our home.</i>

40:56.270 --> 40:58.012
<i> Malcolm: You, head out</i>
<i> to the lake.</i>

40:58.031 --> 41:00.123
<i> Let's get on with it.</i>

41:00.350 --> 41:03.460
<i> No one rests until</i>
<i> we find my corrine.</i>

41:08.133 --> 41:09.949
[thunder crashing]

41:09.968 --> 41:11.885
<i> Olivia: Some we had</i>
<i> already imagined.</i>

41:18.201 --> 41:22.061
[choking]

41:26.376 --> 41:28.443
<i> Olivia: Some we had hidden</i>
<i> from view.</i>

41:34.493 --> 41:36.576
[thunder crashing]

41:41.558 --> 41:44.167
<i> Olivia: And others we couldn't</i>
<i> even dream of.</i>

41:56.998 --> 41:59.182
<i> They would come</i>
<i> to haunt us later.</i>

42:02.412 --> 42:05.913
<i> But in that moment</i>
<i> there was only silence.</i>

42:05.932 --> 42:07.749
<i> My own.</i>

42:08.026 --> 42:08.816
Malcolm: Corrine!

42:10.695 --> 42:11.611
Corrine!

42:16.201 --> 42:17.784
[thunder crashing]

42:18.870 --> 42:19.786
Harry?

42:22.282 --> 42:23.831
<i> What did they do to you?</i>

42:28.713 --> 42:32.623
Don't you worry about me.
I'll be all right.

42:32.717 --> 42:35.701
I should have told the cops
I gave you the watch.

42:35.795 --> 42:38.871
That would've made things worse
for the both of us.

42:38.890 --> 42:40.557
Worse than this?

42:43.286 --> 42:44.644
Look at us.

42:47.290 --> 42:48.982
I miss your playing.

42:53.146 --> 42:54.145
[sighs]

42:54.239 --> 42:56.072
It'll come back.

42:56.299 --> 42:58.074
What if it doesn't?

42:58.301 --> 42:59.158
Hey.

43:00.970 --> 43:02.470
You just sleep now.

43:02.563 --> 43:04.497
We'll worry about
all that later.

43:08.494 --> 43:12.589
[thunder crashes]

43:16.820 --> 43:17.594
Corrine!

43:31.610 --> 43:32.692
Corrine!

43:36.948 --> 43:37.947
Corrine!

43:46.273 --> 43:47.707
Can you stand?

43:50.520 --> 43:51.919
Where does it hurt?

43:54.190 --> 43:57.041
My horse got spooked
and I fell off.

43:57.135 --> 43:59.210
I need to look at the wound
but we're too far out.

43:59.304 --> 44:01.028
We have to find shelter.

44:01.047 --> 44:05.290
There's a chapel
just down that trail.

44:05.310 --> 44:07.977
Okay, hold on.

44:24.996 --> 44:28.498
[thunder crashing]

44:42.180 --> 44:43.404
If no one sees
the beacon outside,

44:43.423 --> 44:45.014
We'll have to sleep here.

44:50.504 --> 44:52.246
I'm going to do
the best I can

44:52.265 --> 44:54.432
But you'll have to be treated by
a doctor as soon as we get back.

44:54.584 --> 44:56.100
I thought you were a doctor.

44:56.252 --> 44:57.610
A qualified trainee.

45:08.540 --> 45:10.039
Relax.

45:11.710 --> 45:13.167
Breathe.

45:19.551 --> 45:22.885
Why don't you tell me how
you knew about this place?

45:23.037 --> 45:25.613
I used to come here
with my brothers.

45:25.706 --> 45:28.707
Are you trying
to distract me?

45:28.727 --> 45:30.393
Is it working?

45:34.381 --> 45:37.567
We used to race our horses all
the way from the house to here.

45:37.718 --> 45:40.978
And who would win,
you or joel?

45:41.130 --> 45:42.530
Not joel.

45:44.968 --> 45:46.200
Mal.

45:50.248 --> 45:51.822
Ever since he died

45:51.916 --> 45:54.751
It's like we're not allowed
to talk about him anymore.

45:57.738 --> 46:00.998
It's like we might break
if we do.

46:01.092 --> 46:02.483
People don't truly break

46:02.502 --> 46:04.594
If someone's there
to help them heal.

46:11.102 --> 46:14.270
I'm done. You can relax.

46:14.497 --> 46:16.272
[sighs]

46:17.776 --> 46:23.337
So, the debt is paid.

46:23.430 --> 46:27.174
I saved your shirt,
you saved my life.

46:27.193 --> 46:30.845
Actually, you ruined
my shirt.

46:30.863 --> 46:33.030
It's wrapped around
your leg.

46:33.124 --> 46:35.699
So, I guess I owe you.

46:35.852 --> 46:38.711
For some reason I still
feel like I owe you.

46:45.878 --> 46:53.292
♪

46:53.386 --> 46:56.938
♪

47:02.895 --> 47:04.070
Malcolm: Corrine!

47:06.049 --> 47:07.448
<i> Corrine!</i>

47:09.160 --> 47:11.569
She's in here!

47:11.663 --> 47:13.746
[thunder crashing]

47:32.925 --> 47:34.742
Oh, thank goodness.

47:34.835 --> 47:36.668
Are you all right?
Can you walk?

47:36.762 --> 47:38.746
Put me down please, daddy.

47:38.839 --> 47:41.006
Just a few scrapes.
She was lucky.

47:41.100 --> 47:42.174
Lucky you found me.

47:42.268 --> 47:45.528
It was you?
Thank you.

47:45.679 --> 47:47.421
I'm so sorry.

47:47.440 --> 47:49.590
As you should be.

47:49.609 --> 47:51.993
I'll call the doctor
in the morning.

47:53.872 --> 47:56.113
I know you don't agree with
all of my choices as a mother,

47:56.265 --> 47:59.024
And many days neither do I.

47:59.043 --> 48:01.693
But I'm doing my best.

48:01.713 --> 48:04.046
Joel will get better
if we let him.

48:09.445 --> 48:12.780
I think I've had enough of
the world outside for one day.

48:12.798 --> 48:14.615
Just want to go to bed.

48:14.708 --> 48:15.966
Of course.

48:16.119 --> 48:18.710
Do you need some help
getting up the stairs?

48:18.730 --> 48:20.563
I think I can manage.

48:23.459 --> 48:24.734
Good night.

48:27.554 --> 48:28.988
Thank you.

48:30.891 --> 48:32.224
How can we ever thank you?

48:32.243 --> 48:33.467
There's no need.

48:33.560 --> 48:36.153
Corrine's safety's
all I care about.

48:36.247 --> 48:37.396
Well, good night.

48:37.490 --> 48:38.897
I have an early start tomorrow.

48:38.917 --> 48:41.083
No, you don't.

48:41.235 --> 48:43.978
You no longer work for me.

48:44.071 --> 48:46.147
You have more than paid
your debt.

48:46.240 --> 48:49.342
From now on your education
is paid for in full.

48:57.009 --> 49:00.010
You should be lying down.

49:00.163 --> 49:02.104
I couldn't lie still
if I tried.

49:02.256 --> 49:03.940
I thought you were done
with the world for today.

49:04.167 --> 49:05.191
I am.

49:07.186 --> 49:08.402
That one.

49:12.858 --> 49:14.525
What we stumbled into
in that storm...

49:14.619 --> 49:15.785
Words like stumbled...

49:15.936 --> 49:17.453
It can never happen again.

49:17.680 --> 49:20.364
You make it sound like
it was an accident.

49:20.458 --> 49:21.457
I'm your uncle.

49:21.608 --> 49:24.627
Half... Uncle.

49:28.374 --> 49:31.542
We lost ourselves.
I was worried about you.

49:31.636 --> 49:33.928
I was just trying to make sure
you were all right.

49:37.216 --> 49:38.866
That wasn't a worried kiss.

49:38.959 --> 49:40.893
It wasn't a proper one either.

49:47.318 --> 49:51.895
You're right.
Um, then it never happened.

49:52.048 --> 49:53.489
I apologize.

49:53.640 --> 49:56.717
You're not the only one
who feels sorry about it.

49:56.736 --> 50:00.645
If you want to be dancing
in time for your ball,

50:00.740 --> 50:02.581
You should get some rest.

50:09.398 --> 50:11.899
What about christopher?

50:11.917 --> 50:15.252
Many debutants have used their
uncles for their first dance.

50:15.404 --> 50:17.346
Or fathers.

50:17.573 --> 50:20.016
It should be someone closer
to her own age.

50:20.167 --> 50:21.333
Since you two have become
so close

50:21.352 --> 50:23.410
I think it's only appropriate.

50:23.429 --> 50:25.429
Christopher is a part
of our family now.

50:25.581 --> 50:26.856
Surely my princess,

50:27.083 --> 50:30.509
You wouldn't mind if I gave you
that first dance.

50:30.528 --> 50:32.936
Christopher, would you do
corrine the honor?

50:33.089 --> 50:35.105
Actually, I was thinking
my friend rockford

50:35.199 --> 50:37.366
Could be my first dance.

50:37.593 --> 50:39.443
Your friend?

50:39.595 --> 50:41.111
You have a male friend.

50:41.205 --> 50:42.496
Rockford taylard.

50:44.024 --> 50:46.042
You knew about this male friend
of hers?

50:50.030 --> 50:51.605
Oh, daddy.

50:51.698 --> 50:53.457
Who doesn't know of
the taylards?

50:53.609 --> 50:56.535
Mr. Taylard owns the textile
mills just outside of town,

50:56.629 --> 50:58.721
And his son rockford

50:58.948 --> 51:02.283
Is just a very sweet
and disciplined young man

51:02.376 --> 51:04.451
Who I happen to have
crossed paths with

51:04.470 --> 51:06.645
At events here and there.

51:08.791 --> 51:09.899
[sighs]

51:10.126 --> 51:11.625
And plus he has just finished
his first year

51:11.718 --> 51:13.736
At the blacksburg school
of business.

51:13.963 --> 51:15.387
Are you sure you want to share
your first dance

51:15.481 --> 51:17.073
With a relative stranger?

51:17.224 --> 51:19.241
Rockford's not a stranger.

51:30.088 --> 51:31.478
Corrine.

51:31.572 --> 51:33.831
You do realize what
you're doing here.

51:33.983 --> 51:35.257
Mother...

51:35.484 --> 51:38.152
I know why you're hesitant,
but rock's changed.

51:38.245 --> 51:40.821
You don't yet know
what changes a man.

51:40.840 --> 51:44.249
He is still the same person
that defiled you.

51:44.268 --> 51:45.917
Remember that.

51:45.937 --> 51:49.012
And remember what we had
to do because of it.

51:49.165 --> 51:52.024
Mrs. Foxworth,
a visitor for you.

51:59.600 --> 52:02.359
Mrs. Steiner?
What a surprise.

52:02.453 --> 52:05.529
I'm going to make this brief
mrs. Foxworth,

52:05.623 --> 52:06.789
Since I don't much enjoy

52:07.016 --> 52:10.684
Being in the company
of a person like you

52:10.777 --> 52:16.373
Who stains the honor of
a great house like this.

52:16.525 --> 52:19.951
I know about
your son's problem.

52:19.971 --> 52:21.053
What problem?

52:23.215 --> 52:26.308
The westmoreland sanitarium.

52:37.880 --> 52:39.563
Three grand.

52:39.715 --> 52:43.233
I'll come by to collect it
next weekend.

52:43.386 --> 52:46.311
Unless, of course, you want
the whole world to find out

52:46.330 --> 52:50.724
That your boy is a...
Homosexual.

52:50.743 --> 52:57.756
♪

53:11.505 --> 53:12.521
How does she know?

53:12.748 --> 53:14.264
The important thing
is that she does

53:14.417 --> 53:16.433
And that she's threatening
to ruin our son.

53:16.527 --> 53:18.919
Joel is in the hospital
trying to get better.

53:18.938 --> 53:21.271
If we don't pay her off
it will all be for nothing.

53:21.365 --> 53:22.531
[sighs]

53:25.110 --> 53:27.536
We can't have your
reputation ruined.

53:29.690 --> 53:32.041
I'll arrange for the money.

53:32.192 --> 53:34.952
...And you care for him?

53:35.104 --> 53:36.695
He's exactly what I need.

53:36.714 --> 53:39.864
The complete opposite to
our overly-complicated family.

53:39.884 --> 53:41.625
No one can change
who they care for,

53:41.777 --> 53:43.177
Not for anything
in the world.

53:47.225 --> 53:49.633
What about me?

53:49.785 --> 53:51.543
Well, of course I care
about you.

53:51.562 --> 53:53.303
Could you from far away?

53:53.456 --> 53:55.956
What are you talking about?

53:55.975 --> 53:57.066
I'm leaving.

53:58.552 --> 54:00.218
What? Why?
You're getting better.

54:00.238 --> 54:01.570
And if I stay here
that won't happen.

54:01.797 --> 54:03.072
Not really.

54:07.152 --> 54:08.577
What about harry?

54:12.250 --> 54:14.208
I don't know.

54:20.983 --> 54:23.592
♪

54:39.518 --> 54:42.278
♪

55:18.707 --> 55:19.315
[twig snaps]

55:20.543 --> 55:21.817
[gasps]

56:33.373 --> 56:37.393
[playing piano hesitantly]
♪

56:37.620 --> 56:48.404
♪

56:51.133 --> 56:52.908
I thought you'd still be
at the office.

56:54.987 --> 56:56.245
I'm leaving.

57:00.476 --> 57:03.401
How did you get out of
the hospital?

57:03.421 --> 57:08.498
I don't want anything and
I'll never bother you again.

57:08.592 --> 57:13.654
If you run, you will never be
welcome back here again.

57:13.672 --> 57:14.930
I know.

57:15.157 --> 57:17.174
I will say that you are
no longer my son.

57:17.326 --> 57:19.601
Well, you were never much
of a father to me anyway.

57:19.753 --> 57:23.180
And I will write you out
of my will.

57:23.274 --> 57:26.108
I don't want your money if
it'd give me a life like yours.

57:31.023 --> 57:33.097
I'll ask you one last time.

57:33.117 --> 57:34.675
How did you get out
of that hospital?

57:34.768 --> 57:38.120
It was me.
I brought him home.

57:48.949 --> 57:50.299
You took him out of
the sanitarium

57:50.450 --> 57:52.526
Without consulting me!

57:52.544 --> 57:53.802
Wait for me.

57:57.808 --> 58:02.144
I went to visit him.
He was unrecognizable.

58:02.371 --> 58:04.313
-We were fixing him.
-We were breaking him.

58:04.464 --> 58:06.482
No, you already did.

58:06.633 --> 58:08.800
Just like you broke
our other son!

58:08.894 --> 58:10.393
Mal's death was
an accident.

58:10.488 --> 58:12.212
Was it?

58:12.305 --> 58:15.048
You are a curse
on this family.

58:15.141 --> 58:18.051
You meddle and our son dies!

58:18.070 --> 58:21.163
You meddle and our other son
becomes an invert!

58:21.390 --> 58:23.240
You meddle and corrine
gets pregnant!

58:23.392 --> 58:25.225
Alicia falls down the stairs!

58:25.244 --> 58:27.728
I get poisoned, and now
that godforsaken housekeeper

58:27.821 --> 58:29.171
Has come back
to blackmail me!

58:29.398 --> 58:30.822
Why?!

58:30.841 --> 58:34.843
Because everything that
you touch, it turns to ash!

58:37.515 --> 58:40.849
And I know you wanted that storm
to take corrine away from me.

58:46.915 --> 58:51.485
Mal died because you assaulted
his fiancée.

58:53.513 --> 58:58.200
Joel was tortured because you
couldn't love him for who he is.

58:58.427 --> 59:00.018
Corrine fell into the arms
of another man

59:00.037 --> 59:02.538
Because she was running
from yours!

59:02.689 --> 59:05.666
You are the curse, malcolm!
You are the storm!

59:11.123 --> 59:13.173
[breathing shakily]

59:14.218 --> 59:16.718
Everything you touch.

59:40.244 --> 59:41.410
What?

59:47.751 --> 59:50.043
I went looking for it
the day after they took you.

59:51.922 --> 59:54.405
I found it beside
the driveway.

59:54.425 --> 59:56.499
The face is busted
but you can pawn it.

59:56.652 --> 59:59.836
Get yourself some money so you
can properly get out of here.

59:59.930 --> 1:00:01.655
With you?

1:00:01.673 --> 1:00:03.390
On your own.

1:00:05.418 --> 1:00:07.752
Thank you for being there
with me.

1:00:07.771 --> 1:00:10.330
For everything.

1:00:10.349 --> 1:00:14.351
I can't make you go through
this next part with me.

1:00:14.503 --> 1:00:16.445
You deserve a life without
memories of this place

1:00:16.672 --> 1:00:18.096
And all I'll do is make you
return to it

1:00:18.190 --> 1:00:20.841
Over and over again.

1:00:20.859 --> 1:00:22.692
Harry, think about
everything being with me
has put you through.

1:00:22.845 --> 1:00:25.454
I have.

1:00:25.681 --> 1:00:27.289
You know, I've been
kicked before.

1:00:27.516 --> 1:00:29.199
It's not the first time
I pushed to the ground.

1:00:29.293 --> 1:00:31.852
I'm, I'm not better yet
but neither are you.

1:00:31.945 --> 1:00:33.203
We get through this together

1:00:33.355 --> 1:00:34.445
Just like we got through
last year.

1:00:34.465 --> 1:00:35.964
That's the point.

1:00:37.801 --> 1:00:39.301
I'm not going to throw
the towel in on you

1:00:39.452 --> 1:00:40.927
Just 'cause you're scared.

1:00:45.476 --> 1:00:50.437
I've got a world to see,
and I got you to see it with.

1:00:52.816 --> 1:00:56.443
Well, where should we
start then?

1:00:59.564 --> 1:01:00.805
New york.

1:01:00.824 --> 1:01:06.069
If it's with you,
I was thinking just...

1:01:06.221 --> 1:01:06.995
"north."

1:01:08.390 --> 1:01:09.998
[both laugh]

1:01:14.505 --> 1:01:16.171
[sighs happily]

1:01:25.257 --> 1:01:28.517
I wish I could force him to
hand over your trust right now.

1:01:32.597 --> 1:01:34.581
This is more than enough.

1:01:34.599 --> 1:01:38.009
Just promise me
you'll live with no regrets.

1:01:38.028 --> 1:01:40.028
Only if you do the same.

1:01:41.273 --> 1:01:42.847
This is going to end
with someone dying.

1:01:42.866 --> 1:01:46.443
Get out of this place.
Save yourself.

1:01:46.537 --> 1:01:48.036
Leave him.

1:01:53.936 --> 1:01:54.835
[sighs]

1:02:06.465 --> 1:02:07.723
Bye, baby.

1:02:19.403 --> 1:02:30.412
♪

1:02:54.830 --> 1:02:57.439
♪

1:03:02.446 --> 1:03:04.428
Mr. Foxworth.

1:03:04.523 --> 1:03:09.192
A pleasure to work together
again after all these years.

1:03:09.286 --> 1:03:10.693
I'm assuming.

1:03:10.788 --> 1:03:12.621
Mrs. Steiner.

1:03:12.772 --> 1:03:15.940
What you fail to understand
about threatening my name

1:03:16.034 --> 1:03:18.535
Is I no longer have a son.

1:03:18.687 --> 1:03:23.632
So, you can blab to whomever
you'd like.

1:03:23.783 --> 1:03:25.300
Very well.

1:03:27.120 --> 1:03:31.789
I can only imagine how important
tonight's party must be to you.

1:03:31.809 --> 1:03:35.477
I hope it goes off
without a hitch.

1:03:40.709 --> 1:03:43.610
♪

1:03:52.404 --> 1:03:53.829
Daddy, where is my dress?

1:03:54.056 --> 1:03:56.556
It was supposed
to arrive yesterday.

1:03:56.649 --> 1:03:59.576
I have bad news,
my darling.

1:03:59.670 --> 1:04:02.003
Your mother...

1:04:02.155 --> 1:04:03.746
[sighs]
...Ruined it.

1:04:03.841 --> 1:04:07.325
Ruined?! How?

1:04:07.344 --> 1:04:10.253
Don't you worry,

1:04:10.347 --> 1:04:13.181
Because I have one last surprise
for your big night.

1:04:28.681 --> 1:04:29.531
Thank you.

1:04:32.094 --> 1:04:33.276
[corinne screaming]

1:04:33.428 --> 1:04:34.327
[gasps]

1:04:52.781 --> 1:04:54.038
Mother!

1:04:54.057 --> 1:04:55.539
Daddy told me what you did
with the dress,

1:04:55.559 --> 1:04:56.799
But don't worry.
I'm not mad at you.

1:04:56.894 --> 1:04:58.209
Well, I had it fixed.

1:04:58.303 --> 1:04:59.227
Daddy said I could wear

1:04:59.454 --> 1:05:00.896
One of grandmother's
dresses instead.

1:05:12.725 --> 1:05:15.301
You brought that down
from the attic?

1:05:15.395 --> 1:05:17.895
This is our daughter's night.

1:05:17.915 --> 1:05:20.582
[sighs heavily]

1:05:25.422 --> 1:05:34.596
♪

1:05:46.168 --> 1:05:49.778
She looks even more beautiful.

1:05:50.839 --> 1:05:51.838
You look...

1:05:51.856 --> 1:05:52.689
Incredible.

1:05:52.841 --> 1:05:54.098
Stunning.

1:05:54.117 --> 1:05:55.675
You're a vision.

1:05:55.694 --> 1:05:58.119
No one will be able to tear
their eyes from you.

1:06:00.290 --> 1:06:02.348
You're right.

1:06:02.367 --> 1:06:06.294
Nothing must distract
from my corrine.

1:06:10.525 --> 1:06:12.133
Not tonight.

1:06:19.142 --> 1:06:19.808
[whistles]

1:06:22.312 --> 1:06:24.145
<i> Malcolm: Take this back</i>
<i> upstairs.</i>

1:06:28.059 --> 1:06:28.984
Go on, now.

1:06:41.498 --> 1:06:43.331
You sure you know
exactly how to do it?

1:06:43.558 --> 1:06:45.483
I think the timing
will be important.

1:06:45.577 --> 1:06:48.819
You just calm down and you have
yourself a good time.

1:06:48.839 --> 1:06:51.080
I know how to talk
to your father.

1:06:51.174 --> 1:06:53.800
We'll show him how great
we are on the dance floor.

1:07:01.518 --> 1:07:03.351
[engine rumbling]

1:07:11.936 --> 1:07:12.861
Thank you.

1:07:13.421 --> 1:07:14.195
Welcome.

1:07:52.294 --> 1:07:55.070
<i> [classical music]</i>
<i> ♪</i>

1:07:55.297 --> 1:08:09.992
<i> ♪</i>

1:08:10.145 --> 1:08:13.146
<i> ♪</i>

1:08:13.164 --> 1:08:15.315
Mrs. Steiner...

1:08:15.333 --> 1:08:19.076
I thought you and mr. Foxworth
had come to an understanding.

1:08:19.096 --> 1:08:24.748
Lest there be any confusion,
you are not welcome here.

1:08:24.843 --> 1:08:28.419
We did, about your son.

1:08:28.438 --> 1:08:32.273
But I'm not here about him.
I'm here about your daughter.

1:08:32.500 --> 1:08:37.612
Or should I say mrs. Alicia
foxworth's daughter.

1:08:37.839 --> 1:08:40.281
<i> ♪</i>

1:08:44.696 --> 1:08:45.695
♪

1:08:45.789 --> 1:08:48.456
What a secret to hold.

1:08:48.608 --> 1:08:52.869
If this gets out, it'll
stain your life forever.

1:08:52.963 --> 1:08:58.800
Everything you've worked so hard
to build will come to pieces.

1:08:59.027 --> 1:09:00.710
But something tells me
you're more worried about

1:09:00.804 --> 1:09:04.213
What will happen to her.

1:09:04.307 --> 1:09:08.476
You don't want her to know
who she is, do you?

1:09:10.480 --> 1:09:13.055
Oh, hello again,
mrs. Steiner.

1:09:13.150 --> 1:09:14.540
Miss foxworth.

1:09:14.634 --> 1:09:16.300
Corrine, where is your father?

1:09:16.319 --> 1:09:19.303
I haven't seen him
since the guests arrived.

1:09:19.397 --> 1:09:20.638
I hope you enjoy yourself.

1:09:20.657 --> 1:09:22.991
Oh, I intend to.

1:09:26.997 --> 1:09:28.746
Right this way.

1:09:33.395 --> 1:09:35.745
<i> [classical music]</i>
<i> ♪</i>

1:09:35.897 --> 1:09:41.918
<i> ♪</i>

1:09:42.012 --> 1:09:44.328
Oh, mr. Foxworth, sir.

1:09:44.422 --> 1:09:45.680
I've been looking for you.

1:09:45.907 --> 1:09:47.515
Mr. Taylard.

1:09:47.742 --> 1:09:51.669
I have something very important
to discuss with you, sir.

1:09:51.763 --> 1:09:54.606
I would like to ask for your
daughter's hand in marriage.

1:09:57.009 --> 1:09:58.193
Let's discuss this in private,
shall we?

1:09:58.420 --> 1:09:59.611
Yeah, sure.

1:10:01.105 --> 1:10:04.324
♪

1:10:06.778 --> 1:10:09.853
A gesture of settling
this amicably.

1:10:09.873 --> 1:10:11.948
I've learned through the years
that this is one of

1:10:12.042 --> 1:10:17.103
The best places for delicate
conversations like these.

1:10:17.196 --> 1:10:20.048
It's how I even kept some
conversations from you.

1:10:30.969 --> 1:10:34.620
How did you hear about
such awful rumors?

1:10:34.714 --> 1:10:37.457
Doctor curtis keeps
detailed records.

1:10:37.475 --> 1:10:39.049
You work for doctor curtis now.

1:10:39.069 --> 1:10:41.310
His notes go all the way back
to the night

1:10:41.463 --> 1:10:44.130
You called him to the house
to look at a pregnant woman

1:10:44.223 --> 1:10:47.075
Who fell down the stairs
for example,

1:10:47.226 --> 1:10:51.153
Where he recorded the woman's
delusional rantings

1:10:51.248 --> 1:10:53.081
For being kept prisoner.

1:10:53.308 --> 1:10:55.733
Doctor curtis doesn't suspect
anything, does he?

1:10:55.752 --> 1:10:56.976
Oh, don't worry.

1:10:57.069 --> 1:10:57.827
[chuckles]

1:10:57.921 --> 1:11:00.421
He's a bit thick.

1:11:00.648 --> 1:11:04.317
But the real tip of the scale,
mrs. Foxworth.

1:11:04.410 --> 1:11:09.989
I mean, look at your daughter
then look at you.

1:11:10.008 --> 1:11:14.394
She's gorgeous
and you're a monster.

1:11:19.834 --> 1:11:21.258
Three thousand then.

1:11:21.278 --> 1:11:22.610
Five.

1:11:25.840 --> 1:11:27.282
I'll get your money.

1:11:54.202 --> 1:11:54.884
Mother...

1:11:55.036 --> 1:11:56.311
Corrine darling, not now.

1:11:56.538 --> 1:11:57.553
I have something very important
I need to discuss

1:11:57.647 --> 1:11:58.704
With your father.

1:11:58.798 --> 1:11:59.814
But I can't find
rockford anywhere

1:11:59.965 --> 1:12:01.816
And the first dance
is about to begin.

1:12:01.967 --> 1:12:05.653
Christopher. Thank goodness.
Would you be so kind?

1:12:08.491 --> 1:12:10.491
It would be my honor.

1:12:20.411 --> 1:12:22.003
-We have a problem.
-Not now.

1:12:22.230 --> 1:12:24.339
Not during corrine's
first dance.

1:12:26.417 --> 1:12:39.187
<i>[orchestra plays "vienna blood"]</i>
<i> ♪</i>

1:12:42.433 --> 1:12:47.678
♪

1:12:47.772 --> 1:12:57.372
♪

1:12:57.523 --> 1:12:59.374
I believe congratulations
are in order.

1:12:59.525 --> 1:13:01.434
You heard.

1:13:01.527 --> 1:13:04.620
He's a lucky man,
wherever he is.

1:13:04.714 --> 1:13:06.047
Don't do that.

1:13:06.274 --> 1:13:07.882
You're not allowed
to be jealous.

1:13:08.109 --> 1:13:12.128
♪

1:13:12.222 --> 1:13:13.129
He stood you up.

1:13:13.281 --> 1:13:14.705
Not after what we agreed.

1:13:14.799 --> 1:13:17.116
You're my uncle, remember?

1:13:17.135 --> 1:13:22.397
♪

1:13:22.548 --> 1:13:24.624
And as your uncle
I wouldn't want you

1:13:24.642 --> 1:13:27.235
To rush into something that
you'll almost certainly regret.

1:13:27.386 --> 1:13:31.072
I'm more than capable
of making my own choices.

1:13:31.299 --> 1:13:33.132
I thought much the same
of myself until...

1:13:33.151 --> 1:13:39.488
♪

1:13:39.641 --> 1:13:42.324
Until I realized otherwise.

1:13:42.419 --> 1:13:45.645
There is no worse pain than
being stuck in a life of regret.

1:13:45.738 --> 1:13:46.587
The gentleman he sounds
as though

1:13:46.739 --> 1:13:49.740
He speaks from experience.

1:13:49.759 --> 1:13:51.759
Do you have any regrets?

1:13:51.986 --> 1:13:53.653
♪

1:13:53.746 --> 1:13:55.321
[applause]

1:13:55.339 --> 1:13:56.722
With you?

1:14:00.678 --> 1:14:01.827
Yes.

1:14:01.846 --> 1:14:12.688
♪

1:14:12.782 --> 1:14:16.842
[applause]

1:14:16.861 --> 1:14:19.787
♪

1:14:20.014 --> 1:14:22.848
I have never been so proud
of you in all my life,

1:14:22.942 --> 1:14:26.777
And you look so
ravishing tonight.

1:14:26.796 --> 1:14:28.779
-Daddy...
-Hmm.

1:14:28.873 --> 1:14:30.948
Has rockford spoken
to you tonight?

1:14:30.967 --> 1:14:37.363
He made his intentions clear
and I made mine clearer.

1:14:37.381 --> 1:14:39.198
Did you hurt him?

1:14:39.217 --> 1:14:41.476
Daddy, what did you do?

1:14:41.627 --> 1:14:44.312
He won't bother you again.

1:14:44.539 --> 1:14:48.224
He abandoned you tonight,
corrine

1:14:48.318 --> 1:14:52.970
And I will never
abandon you.

1:14:53.064 --> 1:14:57.307
Because you...
Belong to me.

1:14:57.401 --> 1:15:04.999
♪

1:15:05.150 --> 1:15:09.420
[applause]

1:15:13.417 --> 1:15:15.343
[applause]

1:15:16.087 --> 1:15:17.753
Corrine, you were incredible

1:15:17.905 --> 1:15:19.755
But I really must speak
with your father.

1:15:19.849 --> 1:15:22.091
Rockford asked daddy
for permission to marry me

1:15:22.185 --> 1:15:25.019
And he scared him away or,
or hurt him, or...

1:15:25.246 --> 1:15:27.021
Please mother,
you have to talk to him.

1:15:27.248 --> 1:15:28.022
Uh...

1:15:31.343 --> 1:15:32.752
Do you love him?

1:15:32.770 --> 1:15:33.694
Rockford?

1:15:35.256 --> 1:15:36.322
Yes.

1:15:37.367 --> 1:15:38.849
You don't really.

1:15:38.868 --> 1:15:41.277
You think you do,
you really think you do,

1:15:41.371 --> 1:15:43.037
But you don't.

1:15:43.188 --> 1:15:47.024
He's just a door to a life
you think you want.

1:15:47.043 --> 1:15:52.547
But trust me, behind it
is no life at all.

1:15:52.698 --> 1:15:54.197
How can you be sure?

1:15:54.292 --> 1:15:57.701
I can see it in your eyes.
You're not in love with him.

1:15:57.795 --> 1:15:59.278
But when you really know,

1:15:59.297 --> 1:16:01.389
When you find someone
you really love,

1:16:01.540 --> 1:16:04.967
I will support you
no matter what.

1:16:05.061 --> 1:16:07.061
[tearfully] this was supposed
to be my night.

1:16:11.067 --> 1:16:11.899
Excuse me.

1:16:15.905 --> 1:16:17.296
Mrs. Steiner is here.

1:16:17.389 --> 1:16:19.740
I've locked her
in the library.

1:16:19.892 --> 1:16:21.224
Why would you do that?

1:16:21.319 --> 1:16:24.061
Because she knows
about corrine.

1:16:24.080 --> 1:16:25.413
Knows about what?

1:16:40.004 --> 1:16:41.487
You're an animal.

1:16:41.580 --> 1:16:43.264
I apologize for resorting
to these methods

1:16:43.415 --> 1:16:44.673
But you left me no choice.

1:16:44.767 --> 1:16:45.991
A wild animal.

1:16:46.010 --> 1:16:47.584
I had to find my husband.

1:16:47.604 --> 1:16:49.845
He's on his way now with
your money, I can assure you.

1:16:49.997 --> 1:16:51.922
Exactly how do you expect me
to trust you

1:16:51.941 --> 1:16:55.184
After you kept me locked
in that closet for an hour?

1:16:55.278 --> 1:16:57.612
And what's to stop me
from going out there right now

1:16:57.763 --> 1:16:59.614
To make a little toast
of my own?

1:16:59.765 --> 1:17:01.782
Just know, mrs. Steiner,

1:17:01.934 --> 1:17:04.768
What you seek to destroy,
it's all I have.

1:17:04.787 --> 1:17:06.603
A life built on lies.

1:17:06.623 --> 1:17:08.197
Maybe.

1:17:08.291 --> 1:17:10.199
But it's all I could manage
given the circumstances.

1:17:10.293 --> 1:17:12.793
Everything I've done,
every choice I've made,

1:17:13.020 --> 1:17:17.706
Good, bad, or somewhere
in between.

1:17:17.859 --> 1:17:19.133
It's all been
for my children.

1:17:19.284 --> 1:17:21.802
Corrine is not your child.

1:17:21.954 --> 1:17:24.713
She may not be of my flesh
but she is of my heart.

1:17:24.807 --> 1:17:28.291
[laughs heartily]

1:17:28.311 --> 1:17:30.703
Who do you think
you're fooling.

1:17:30.721 --> 1:17:32.538
People talk.

1:17:32.631 --> 1:17:34.315
Everyone knows that deep down

1:17:34.466 --> 1:17:40.229
You're jealous of corrine
for her beauty, for her charm.

1:17:40.381 --> 1:17:46.051
For the fact that she'll have
a love in her life unlike you.

1:17:46.145 --> 1:17:49.238
What do you know about love?

1:17:49.332 --> 1:17:52.908
Do you think garland
ever loved you in return?

1:17:53.002 --> 1:17:56.987
Oh, my apologies, you knew him
as mr. Foxworth

1:17:57.081 --> 1:18:00.991
And he knew you as the woman
who cleaned his chamber pot.

1:18:01.010 --> 1:18:02.418
How dare you?

1:18:02.570 --> 1:18:05.421
This is my house.
I'll dare to do as I please.

1:18:05.573 --> 1:18:08.832
I think I'll go find
mr. Foxworth on my own.

1:18:08.851 --> 1:18:09.850
Stop!

1:18:12.763 --> 1:18:13.979
[gasps]

1:18:15.416 --> 1:18:16.857
[door opens]

1:18:21.847 --> 1:18:24.924
She was going
to tell everyone.

1:18:24.942 --> 1:18:26.534
We have to call a doctor.

1:18:30.765 --> 1:18:31.539
Shh.

1:18:45.947 --> 1:18:47.221
[whacks]

1:18:48.799 --> 1:18:49.724
[gasps]

1:19:32.843 --> 1:19:36.845
[out of breath]

1:19:36.998 --> 1:19:38.939
Our guests are waiting.

1:19:41.502 --> 1:19:42.943
Shall we?

1:19:51.195 --> 1:19:53.770
<i> [orchestral dance music]</i>
♪

1:19:53.790 --> 1:20:08.636
♪

1:20:08.863 --> 1:20:28.656
♪

1:20:28.883 --> 1:20:38.999
♪

1:20:39.226 --> 1:20:53.997
♪

1:20:54.016 --> 1:21:14.017
♪

1:21:14.036 --> 1:21:22.501
♪

1:21:33.797 --> 1:21:35.055
-Oh.
-Sorry.

1:21:36.450 --> 1:21:39.393
What are you doing?

1:21:39.544 --> 1:21:43.122
Never mind. It's none
of my business.

1:21:43.215 --> 1:21:46.049
Enjoy the rest
of your evening.

1:21:46.068 --> 1:21:47.735
The engagement's off.

1:21:51.966 --> 1:21:54.466
I'm not really sure it was
ever really on, but...

1:21:54.485 --> 1:21:55.743
I'm sorry.

1:21:56.746 --> 1:21:58.203
Are you?

1:22:01.492 --> 1:22:03.417
Not at all.

1:22:03.644 --> 1:22:07.570
I have tried so hard
to make it work.

1:22:07.590 --> 1:22:09.590
To move on,
to forget about-

1:22:12.002 --> 1:22:13.318
But fighting what I feel inside

1:22:13.337 --> 1:22:15.387
Has become more difficult
than facing it.

1:22:20.494 --> 1:22:21.418
You.

1:22:21.437 --> 1:22:23.162
Stop.

1:22:23.180 --> 1:22:24.513
You're what I feel inside.

1:22:24.665 --> 1:22:25.681
Please.

1:22:25.833 --> 1:22:27.107
You're what I want.

1:22:27.259 --> 1:22:28.091
[softly]
don't.

1:22:28.110 --> 1:22:29.610
You're who I love.

1:22:30.947 --> 1:22:32.446
Do you love me?

1:22:41.940 --> 1:22:43.624
Of course I love you.

1:22:48.447 --> 1:22:50.464
So, what do we do now?

1:22:56.973 --> 1:22:59.974
♪

1:23:12.046 --> 1:23:14.488
<i> Olivia: Keeping up an illusion</i>
<i> is hard work.</i>

1:23:22.147 --> 1:23:23.622
<i> Back-breaking work.</i>

1:23:25.835 --> 1:23:27.334
[grunts]

1:23:32.991 --> 1:23:34.842
<i> Heartbreaking work.</i>

1:23:38.405 --> 1:23:40.014
<i> Teamwork.</i>

1:23:44.762 --> 1:23:47.187
<i> At breakfast you want</i>
<i> to kill your husband.</i>

1:23:53.103 --> 1:23:56.697
<i> By bedtime you're helping</i>
<i> him bury someone else's body.</i>

1:24:13.457 --> 1:24:15.841
<i> But something keeps you</i>
<i> going through it.</i>

1:24:36.721 --> 1:24:38.572
Get some rest.

1:24:47.157 --> 1:24:52.419
♪

1:24:55.574 --> 1:24:59.576
<i>Olivia: The thought that all of</i>
<i> the blood and dirt and lies</i>

1:24:59.670 --> 1:25:01.428
<i> Would be worth it.</i>

1:25:07.845 --> 1:25:10.938
<i> But in the end,</i>
<i>because of everything I did...</i>

1:25:14.168 --> 1:25:16.443
<i> Their lives will be better</i>
<i> than mine.</i>

1:25:23.786 --> 1:25:25.452
<i> My children.</i>

1:25:28.124 --> 1:25:34.128
♪

1:25:39.969 --> 1:25:43.362
<i> Joel got out of</i>
<i> foxworth hall alive.</i>

1:25:43.455 --> 1:25:45.806
<i> Surely corrine could too.</i>

1:25:48.811 --> 1:25:54.314
[heavy breathing sounds]

1:26:01.398 --> 1:26:04.950
<i>But I was learning the hard way</i>
<i>that my home had too many doors.</i>

1:26:11.316 --> 1:26:13.959
<i> Old ones. New ones.</i>

1:26:21.993 --> 1:26:24.636
<i> Behind each a place to hide.</i>

1:26:32.413 --> 1:26:36.264
<i>That night, each and every one</i>
<i> of foxworth hall's doors</i>

1:26:36.358 --> 1:26:38.025
<i> Would fly open.</i>

1:26:40.754 --> 1:26:43.363
<i> And there would be</i>
<i> no hiding anymore.</i>
